00198 /*
00199    Flags/methods for returning states.
00200 
00201    The SWIG conversion methods, as ConvertPtr, return an integer
00202    that tells if the conversion was successful or not. And if not,
00203    an error code can be returned (see swigerrors.swg for the codes).
00204 
00205    Use the following macros/flags to set or process the returning
00206    states.
00207 
00208    In old versions of SWIG, code such as the following was usually written:
00209 
00210      if (SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags) != -1) {
00211        // success code
00212      } else {
00213        //fail code
00214      }
00215 
00216    Now you can be more explicit:
00217 
00218     int res = SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags);
00219     if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
00220       // success code
00221     } else {
00222       // fail code
00223     }
00224 
00225    which is the same really, but now you can also do
00226 
00227     Type *ptr;
00228     int res = SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,(void **)(&ptr),ty.flags);
00229     if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
00230       // success code
00231       if (SWIG_IsNewObj(res) {
00232         ...
00233         delete *ptr;
00234       } else {
00235         ...
00236       }
00237     } else {
00238       // fail code
00239     }
00240 
00241    I.e., now SWIG_ConvertPtr can return new objects and you can
00242    identify the case and take care of the deallocation. Of course that
00243    also requires SWIG_ConvertPtr to return new result values, such as
00244 
00245       int SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj, ptr,...) {
00246         if (<obj is ok>) {
00247           if (<need new object>) {
00248             *ptr = <ptr to new allocated object>;
00249             return SWIG_NEWOBJ;
00250           } else {
00251             *ptr = <ptr to old object>;
00252             return SWIG_OLDOBJ;
00253           }
00254         } else {
00255           return SWIG_BADOBJ;
00256         }
00257       }
00258 
00259    Of course, returning the plain '0(success)/-1(fail)' still works, but you can be
00260    more explicit by returning SWIG_BADOBJ, SWIG_ERROR or any of the
00261    SWIG errors code.
00262 
00263    Finally, if the SWIG_CASTRANK_MODE is enabled, the result code
00264    allows to return the 'cast rank', for example, if you have this
00265 
00266        int food(double)
00267        int fooi(int);
00268 
00269    and you call
00270 
00271       food(1)   // cast rank '1'  (1 -> 1.0)
00272       fooi(1)   // cast rank '0'
00273 
00274    just use the SWIG_AddCast()/SWIG_CheckState()
00275 */
00276 
00277 #define SWIG_OK                    (0)
00278 #define SWIG_ERROR                 (-1)
00279 #define SWIG_IsOK(r)               (r >= 0)
00280 #define SWIG_ArgError(r)           ((r != SWIG_ERROR) ? r : SWIG_TypeError)
00281 
00282 /* The CastRankLimit says how many bits are used for the cast rank */
00283 #define SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT         (1 << 8)
00284 /* The NewMask denotes the object was created (using new/malloc) */
00285 #define SWIG_NEWOBJMASK            (SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT  << 1)
00286 /* The TmpMask is for in/out typemaps that use temporal objects */
00287 #define SWIG_TMPOBJMASK            (SWIG_NEWOBJMASK << 1)
00288 /* Simple returning values */
00289 #define SWIG_BADOBJ                (SWIG_ERROR)
00290 #define SWIG_OLDOBJ                (SWIG_OK)
00291 #define SWIG_NEWOBJ                (SWIG_OK | SWIG_NEWOBJMASK)
00292 #define SWIG_TMPOBJ                (SWIG_OK | SWIG_TMPOBJMASK)
00293 /* Check, add and del mask methods */
00294 #define SWIG_AddNewMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r | SWIG_NEWOBJMASK) : r)
00295 #define SWIG_DelNewMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r & ~SWIG_NEWOBJMASK) : r)
00296 #define SWIG_IsNewObj(r)           (SWIG_IsOK(r) && (r & SWIG_NEWOBJMASK))
00297 #define SWIG_AddTmpMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r | SWIG_TMPOBJMASK) : r)
00298 #define SWIG_DelTmpMask(r)         (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r & ~SWIG_TMPOBJMASK) : r)
00299 #define SWIG_IsTmpObj(r)           (SWIG_IsOK(r) && (r & SWIG_TMPOBJMASK))
00300 
00301 /* Cast-Rank Mode */
00302 #if defined(SWIG_CASTRANK_MODE)
00303 #  ifndef SWIG_TypeRank
00304 #    define SWIG_TypeRank             unsigned long
00305 #  endif
00306 #  ifndef SWIG_MAXCASTRANK            /* Default cast allowed */
00307 #    define SWIG_MAXCASTRANK          (2)
00308 #  endif
00309 #  define SWIG_CASTRANKMASK          ((SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT) -1)
00310 #  define SWIG_CastRank(r)           (r & SWIG_CASTRANKMASK)
00311 SWIGINTERNINLINE int SWIG_AddCast(int r) {
00312   return SWIG_IsOK(r) ? ((SWIG_CastRank(r) < SWIG_MAXCASTRANK) ? (r + 1) : SWIG_ERROR) : r;
00313 }
00314 SWIGINTERNINLINE int SWIG_CheckState(int r) {
00315   return SWIG_IsOK(r) ? SWIG_CastRank(r) + 1 : 0;
00316 }
00317 #else /* no cast-rank mode */
00318 #  define SWIG_AddCast(r) (r)
00319 #  define SWIG_CheckState(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? 1 : 0)
00320 #endif

00333 typedef struct swig_type_info {
00334   const char             *name;                 /* mangled name of this type */
00335   const char             *str;                  /* human readable name of this type */

00342 /* Structure to store a type and conversion function used for casting */
00343 typedef struct swig_cast_info {
00344   swig_type_info         *type;                 /* pointer to type that is equivalent to this type */
00345   swig_converter_func     converter;            /* function to cast the void pointers */
00346   struct swig_cast_info  *next;                 /* pointer to next cast in linked list */
00347   struct swig_cast_info  *prev;                 /* pointer to the previous cast */

00350 /* Structure used to store module information
00351  * Each module generates one structure like this, and the runtime collects
00352  * all of these structures and stores them in a circularly linked list.*/
00353 typedef struct swig_module_info {
00354   swig_type_info         **types;               /* Array of pointers to swig_type_info structures that are in this module */
00355   size_t                 size;                  /* Number of types in this module */
00356   struct swig_module_info *next;                /* Pointer to next element in circularly linked list */
00357   swig_type_info         **type_initial;        /* Array of initially generated type structures */
00358   swig_cast_info         **cast_initial;        /* Array of initially generated casting structures */
00359   void                    *clientdata;          /* Language specific module data */
00360 } swig_module_info;

00362 /*
00363   Compare two type names skipping the space characters, therefore
00364   "char*" == "char *" and "Class<int>" == "Class<int >", etc.
00365 
00366   Return 0 when the two name types are equivalent, as in
00367   strncmp, but skipping ' '.
00368 */
00369 SWIGRUNTIME int
00370 SWIG_TypeNameComp(const char *f1, const char *l1,
00371                   const char *f2, const char *l2) {
00372   for (;(f1 != l1) && (f2 != l2); ++f1, ++f2) {
00373     while ((*f1 == ' ') && (f1 != l1)) ++f1;
00374     while ((*f2 == ' ') && (f2 != l2)) ++f2;
00375     if (*f1 != *f2) return (*f1 > *f2) ? 1 : -1;
00376   }
00377   return (int)((l1 - f1) - (l2 - f2));
00378 }

00380 /*
00381   Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...
00382   Return 0 if equal, -1 if nb < tb, 1 if nb > tb
00383 */
00384 SWIGRUNTIME int
00385 SWIG_TypeCmp(const char *nb, const char *tb) {
00386   int equiv = 1;
00387   const char* te = tb + strlen(tb);
00388   const char* ne = nb;
00389   while (equiv != 0 && *ne) {
00390     for (nb = ne; *ne; ++ne) {
00391       if (*ne == '|') break;
00392     }
00393     equiv = SWIG_TypeNameComp(nb, ne, tb, te);
00394     if (*ne) ++ne;
00395   }
00396   return equiv;
00397 }
00398 
00399 /*
00400   Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...
00401   Return 0 if not equal, 1 if equal
00402 */
00403 SWIGRUNTIME int
00404 SWIG_TypeEquiv(const char *nb, const char *tb) {
00405   return SWIG_TypeCmp(nb, tb) == 0 ? 1 : 0;
00406 }

00408 /*
00409   Check the typename
00410 */
00411 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
00412 SWIG_TypeCheck(const char *c, swig_type_info *ty) {
00413   if (ty) {
00414     swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;
00415     while (iter) {
00416       if (strcmp(iter->type->name, c) == 0) {
00417         if (iter == ty->cast)
00418           return iter;
00419         /* Move iter to the top of the linked list */
00420         iter->prev->next = iter->next;
00421         if (iter->next)
00422           iter->next->prev = iter->prev;
00423         iter->next = ty->cast;
00424         iter->prev = 0;
00425         if (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;
00426         ty->cast = iter;
00427         return iter;
00428       }
00429       iter = iter->next;
00430     }
00431   }
00432   return 0;
00433 }

00435 /*
00436   Identical to SWIG_TypeCheck, except strcmp is replaced with a pointer comparison
00437 */
00438 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
00439 SWIG_TypeCheckStruct(swig_type_info *from, swig_type_info *ty) {
00440   if (ty) {
00441     swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;
00442     while (iter) {
00443       if (iter->type == from) {
00444         if (iter == ty->cast)
00445           return iter;
00446         /* Move iter to the top of the linked list */
00447         iter->prev->next = iter->next;
00448         if (iter->next)
00449           iter->next->prev = iter->prev;
00450         iter->next = ty->cast;
00451         iter->prev = 0;
00452         if (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;
00453         ty->cast = iter;
00454         return iter;
00455       }
00456       iter = iter->next;
00457     }
00458   }
00459   return 0;
00460 }

00462 /*
00463   Cast a pointer up an inheritance hierarchy
00464 */
00465 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE void *
00466 SWIG_TypeCast(swig_cast_info *ty, void *ptr, int *newmemory) {
00467   return ((!ty) || (!ty->converter)) ? ptr : (*ty->converter)(ptr, newmemory);
00468 }

00470 /*
00471    Dynamic pointer casting. Down an inheritance hierarchy
00472 */
00473 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00474 SWIG_TypeDynamicCast(swig_type_info *ty, void **ptr) {
00475   swig_type_info *lastty = ty;
00476   if (!ty || !ty->dcast) return ty;
00477   while (ty && (ty->dcast)) {
00478     ty = (*ty->dcast)(ptr);
00479     if (ty) lastty = ty;
00480   }
00481   return lastty;
00482 }

00492 /*
00493   Return the pretty name associated with this type,
00494   that is an unmangled type name in a form presentable to the user.
00495 */
00496 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00497 SWIG_TypePrettyName(const swig_type_info *type) {
00498   /* The "str" field contains the equivalent pretty names of the
00499      type, separated by vertical-bar characters.  We choose
00500      to print the last name, as it is often (?) the most
00501      specific. */
00502   if (!type) return NULL;
00503   if (type->str != NULL) {
00504     const char *last_name = type->str;
00505     const char *s;
00506     for (s = type->str; *s; s++)
00507       if (*s == '|') last_name = s+1;
00508     return last_name;
00509   }
00510   else
00511     return type->name;
00512 }

00514 /*
00515    Set the clientdata field for a type
00516 */
00517 SWIGRUNTIME void
00518 SWIG_TypeClientData(swig_type_info *ti, void *clientdata) {
00519   swig_cast_info *cast = ti->cast;
00520   /* if (ti->clientdata == clientdata) return; */
00521   ti->clientdata = clientdata;
00522 
00523   while (cast) {
00524     if (!cast->converter) {
00525       swig_type_info *tc = cast->type;
00526       if (!tc->clientdata) {
00527         SWIG_TypeClientData(tc, clientdata);
00528       }
00529     }
00530     cast = cast->next;
00531   }
00532 }
00533 SWIGRUNTIME void
00534 SWIG_TypeNewClientData(swig_type_info *ti, void *clientdata) {
00535   SWIG_TypeClientData(ti, clientdata);
00536   ti->owndata = 1;
00537 }

00539 /*
00540   Search for a swig_type_info structure only by mangled name
00541   Search is a O(log #types)
00542 
00543   We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.
00544   Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around
00545   the circular list.
00546 */
00547 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00548 SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start,
00549                             swig_module_info *end,
00550                             const char *name) {
00551   swig_module_info *iter = start;
00552   do {
00553     if (iter->size) {
00554       register size_t l = 0;
00555       register size_t r = iter->size - 1;
00556       do {
00557         /* since l+r >= 0, we can (>> 1) instead (/ 2) */
00558         register size_t i = (l + r) >> 1;
00559         const char *iname = iter->types[i]->name;
00560         if (iname) {
00561           register int compare = strcmp(name, iname);
00562           if (compare == 0) {
00563             return iter->types[i];
00564           } else if (compare < 0) {
00565             if (i) {
00566               r = i - 1;
00567             } else {
00568               break;
00569             }
00570           } else if (compare > 0) {
00571             l = i + 1;
00572           }
00573         } else {
00574           break; /* should never happen */
00575         }
00576       } while (l <= r);
00577     }
00578     iter = iter->next;
00579   } while (iter != end);
00580   return 0;
00581 }
00582 
00583 /*
00584   Search for a swig_type_info structure for either a mangled name or a human readable name.
00585   It first searches the mangled names of the types, which is a O(log #types)
00586   If a type is not found it then searches the human readable names, which is O(#types).
00587 
00588   We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.
00589   Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around
00590   the circular list.
00591 */
00592 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
00593 SWIG_TypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start,
00594                      swig_module_info *end,
00595                      const char *name) {
00596   /* STEP 1: Search the name field using binary search */
00597   swig_type_info *ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(start, end, name);
00598   if (ret) {
00599     return ret;
00600   } else {
00601     /* STEP 2: If the type hasn't been found, do a complete search
00602        of the str field (the human readable name) */
00603     swig_module_info *iter = start;
00604     do {
00605       register size_t i = 0;
00606       for (; i < iter->size; ++i) {
00607         if (iter->types[i]->str && (SWIG_TypeEquiv(iter->types[i]->str, name)))
00608           return iter->types[i];
00609       }
00610       iter = iter->next;
00611     } while (iter != end);
00612   }
00613 
00614   /* neither found a match */
00615   return 0;
00616 }
00617 
00618 /*
00619    Pack binary data into a string
00620 */
00621 SWIGRUNTIME char *
00622 SWIG_PackData(char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz) {
00623   static const char hex[17] = "0123456789abcdef";
00624   register const unsigned char *u = (unsigned char *) ptr;
00625   register const unsigned char *eu =  u + sz;
00626   for (; u != eu; ++u) {
00627     register unsigned char uu = *u;
00628     *(c++) = hex[(uu & 0xf0) >> 4];
00629     *(c++) = hex[uu & 0xf];
00630   }
00631   return c;
00632 }
00633 
00634 /*
00635    Unpack binary data from a string
00636 */
00637 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00638 SWIG_UnpackData(const char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz) {
00639   register unsigned char *u = (unsigned char *) ptr;
00640   register const unsigned char *eu = u + sz;
00641   for (; u != eu; ++u) {
00642     register char d = *(c++);
00643     register unsigned char uu;
00644     if ((d >= '0') && (d <= '9'))
00645       uu = ((d - '0') << 4);
00646     else if ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f'))
00647       uu = ((d - ('a'-10)) << 4);
00648     else
00649       return (char *) 0;
00650     d = *(c++);
00651     if ((d >= '0') && (d <= '9'))
00652       uu |= (d - '0');
00653     else if ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f'))
00654       uu |= (d - ('a'-10));
00655     else
00656       return (char *) 0;
00657     *u = uu;
00658   }
00659   return c;
00660 }
00661 
00662 /*
00663    Pack 'void *' into a string buffer.
00664 */
00665 SWIGRUNTIME char *
00666 SWIG_PackVoidPtr(char *buff, void *ptr, const char *name, size_t bsz) {
00667   char *r = buff;
00668   if ((2*sizeof(void *) + 2) > bsz) return 0;
00669   *(r++) = '_';
00670   r = SWIG_PackData(r,&ptr,sizeof(void *));
00671   if (strlen(name) + 1 > (bsz - (r - buff))) return 0;
00672   strcpy(r,name);
00673   return buff;
00674 }
00675 
00676 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00677 SWIG_UnpackVoidPtr(const char *c, void **ptr, const char *name) {
00678   if (*c != '_') {
00679     if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) {
00680       *ptr = (void *) 0;
00681       return name;
00682     } else {
00683       return 0;
00684     }
00685   }
00686   return SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sizeof(void *));
00687 }
00688 
00689 SWIGRUNTIME char *
00690 SWIG_PackDataName(char *buff, void *ptr, size_t sz, const char *name, size_t bsz) {
00691   char *r = buff;
00692   size_t lname = (name ? strlen(name) : 0);
00693   if ((2*sz + 2 + lname) > bsz) return 0;
00694   *(r++) = '_';
00695   r = SWIG_PackData(r,ptr,sz);
00696   if (lname) {
00697     strncpy(r,name,lname+1);
00698   } else {
00699     *r = 0;
00700   }
00701   return buff;
00702 }
00703 
00704 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
00705 SWIG_UnpackDataName(const char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz, const char *name) {
00706   if (*c != '_') {
00707     if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) {
00708       memset(ptr,0,sz);
00709       return name;
00710     } else {
00711       return 0;
00712     }
00713   }
00714   return SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sz);
00715 }

00718 }

00771 /* History of Lua C API length functions:  In Lua 5.0 (and before?)
00772    there was "lua_strlen".  In Lua 5.1, this was renamed "lua_objlen",
00773    but a compatibility define of "lua_strlen" was added.  In Lua 5.2,
00774    this function was again renamed, to "lua_rawlen" (to emphasize that
00775    it doesn't call the "__len" metamethod), and the compatibility
00776    define of lua_strlen was removed.  All SWIG uses have been updated
00777    to "lua_rawlen", and we add our own defines of that here for older
00778    versions of Lua.  */
00779 #if !defined(LUA_VERSION_NUM) || LUA_VERSION_NUM < 501
00780 # define lua_rawlen lua_strlen
00781 #elif LUA_VERSION_NUM == 501
00782 # define lua_rawlen lua_objlen
00783 #endif

00788    lua_pushglobaltable ourselves for Lua versions before 5.2.  */
00789 #if !defined(LUA_VERSION_NUM) || LUA_VERSION_NUM < 502
00790 # define lua_pushglobaltable(L) lua_pushvalue(L, LUA_GLOBALSINDEX)
00791 #endif

00798 /* Push the string STR on the Lua stack, like lua_pushstring, but
00799    prefixed with the the location of the innermost Lua call-point
00800    (as formated by luaL_where).  */
00801 SWIGRUNTIME void
00802 SWIG_Lua_pusherrstring (lua_State *L, const char *str)
00803 {
00804   luaL_where (L, 1);
00805   lua_pushstring (L, str);
00806   lua_concat (L, 2);
00807 }
00808 
00809 /* Push a formatted string generated from FMT and following args on
00810    the Lua stack, like lua_pushfstring, but prefixed with the the
00811    location of the innermost Lua call-point (as formated by luaL_where).  */
00812 SWIGRUNTIME void
00813 SWIG_Lua_pushferrstring (lua_State *L, const char *fmt, ...)
00814 {
00815   va_list argp;
00816   va_start(argp, fmt);
00817   luaL_where(L, 1);
00818   lua_pushvfstring(L, fmt, argp);
00819   va_end(argp);
00820   lua_concat(L, 2);
00821 }

00952 /* storing/access of swig_module_info */
00953 SWIGRUNTIME swig_module_info *
00954 SWIG_Lua_GetModule(lua_State* L) {
00955   swig_module_info *ret = 0;
00956   lua_pushstring(L,"swig_runtime_data_type_pointer" SWIG_RUNTIME_VERSION SWIG_TYPE_TABLE_NAME);
00957   lua_rawget(L,LUA_REGISTRYINDEX);
00958   if (lua_islightuserdata(L,-1))
00959     ret=(swig_module_info*)lua_touserdata(L,-1);
00960   lua_pop(L,1);  /* tidy */
00961   return ret;
00962 }

00964 SWIGRUNTIME void
00965 SWIG_Lua_SetModule(lua_State* L, swig_module_info *module) {
00966   /* add this all into the Lua registry: */
00967   lua_pushstring(L,"swig_runtime_data_type_pointer" SWIG_RUNTIME_VERSION SWIG_TYPE_TABLE_NAME);
00968   lua_pushlightuserdata(L,(void*)module);
00969   lua_rawset(L,LUA_REGISTRYINDEX);
00970 }

00976 /* this function is called when trying to set an immutable.
00977 default action is to print an error.
00978 This can removed with a compile flag SWIGLUA_IGNORE_SET_IMMUTABLE */
00979 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_set_immutable(lua_State* L)
00980 {
00981 /*  there should be 1 param passed in: the new value */
00982 #ifndef SWIGLUA_IGNORE_SET_IMMUTABLE
00983   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove it */
00984   luaL_error(L,"This variable is immutable");
00985 #endif
00986     return 0;   /* should not return anything */
00987 }
00988 
00989 /* the module.get method used for getting linked data */
00990 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_module_get(lua_State* L)
00991 {
00992 /*  there should be 2 params passed in
00993   (1) table (not the meta table)
00994   (2) string name of the attribute
00995   printf("SWIG_Lua_module_get %p(%s) '%s'\n",
00996    lua_topointer(L,1),lua_typename(L,lua_type(L,1)),
00997    lua_tostring(L,2));
00998 */
00999   /* get the metatable */
01000 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01001   assert(lua_isrotable(L,1)); /* just in case */
01002 #else
01003   assert(lua_istable(L,1)); /* default Lua action */
01004 #endif
01005   lua_getmetatable(L,1);  /* get the metatable */
01006 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01007   assert(lua_isrotable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01008 #else
01009   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01010 #endif
01011   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".get");  /* get the .get table */
01012   lua_remove(L,3);  /* remove metatable */
01013 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01014   if (lua_isrotable(L,-1))
01015 #else
01016   if (lua_istable(L,-1))
01017 #endif
01018   {
01019     /* look for the key in the .get table */
01020     lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01021     lua_rawget(L,-2);
01022     lua_remove(L,3);  /* remove .get */
01023     if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))
01024     {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01025       lua_call(L,0,1);
01026       return 1;
01027     }
01028     lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the top */
01029   }
01030   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the .get */
01031   lua_pushnil(L);  /* return a nil */
01032   return 1;
01033 }
01034 
01035 /* the module.set method used for setting linked data */
01036 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_module_set(lua_State* L)
01037 {
01038 /*  there should be 3 params passed in
01039   (1) table (not the meta table)
01040   (2) string name of the attribute
01041   (3) any for the new value
01042 */
01043   /* get the metatable */
01044 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01045   assert(lua_isrotable(L,1));  /* just in case */
01046 #else
01047   assert(lua_istable(L,1)); /* default Lua action */
01048 #endif
01049   lua_getmetatable(L,1);  /* get the metatable */
01050 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01051   assert(lua_isrotable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01052 #else
01053   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01054 #endif
01055   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".set");  /* get the .set table */
01056   lua_remove(L,4);  /* remove metatable */
01057 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01058   if (lua_isrotable(L,-1))
01059 #else
01060   if (lua_istable(L,-1))
01061 #endif
01062   {
01063     /* look for the key in the .set table */
01064     lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01065     lua_rawget(L,-2);
01066     lua_remove(L,4);  /* remove .set */
01067     if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))
01068     {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01069       lua_pushvalue(L,3);  /* value */
01070       lua_call(L,1,0);
01071       return 0;
01072     }
01073 #if (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) 
01074     else {
01075       return 0; // Exits stoically if an invalid key is initialized.
01076     }
01077 #endif
01078   }
01079   lua_settop(L,3);  /* reset back to start */
01080   /* we now have the table, key & new value, so just set directly */
01081   lua_rawset(L,1);  /* add direct */
01082   return 0;
01083 }
01084 
01085 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) && (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01086 /* registering a module in lua. Pushes the module table on the stack. */
01087 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_module_begin(lua_State* L,const char* name)
01088 {
01089   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01090   lua_pushstring(L,name);
01091   lua_newtable(L);   /* the table */
01092   /* add meta table */
01093   lua_newtable(L);    /* the meta table */
01094   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__index",SWIG_Lua_module_get);
01095   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__newindex",SWIG_Lua_module_set);
01096   lua_pushstring(L,".get");
01097   lua_newtable(L);    /* the .get table */
01098   lua_rawset(L,-3);  /* add .get into metatable */
01099   lua_pushstring(L,".set");
01100   lua_newtable(L);    /* the .set table */
01101   lua_rawset(L,-3);  /* add .set into metatable */
01102   lua_setmetatable(L,-2);  /* sets meta table in module */
01103 #ifdef SWIG_LUA_MODULE_GLOBAL
01104   /* If requested, install the module directly into the global namespace. */
01105   lua_rawset(L,-3);        /* add module into parent */
01106   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,name);   /* get the table back out */
01107 #else
01108   /* Do not install the module table as global name. The stack top has
01109      the module table with the name below. We pop the top and replace
01110      the name with it. */
01111   lua_replace(L,-2);
01112 #endif
01113 }
01114 
01115 /* ending the register */
01116 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_module_end(lua_State* L)
01117 {
01118   lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove module) */
01119 }
01120 
01121 /* adding a linked variable to the module */
01122 SWIGINTERN void SWIG_Lua_module_add_variable(lua_State* L,const char* name,lua_CFunction getFn,lua_CFunction setFn)
01123 {
01124   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01125   lua_getmetatable(L,-1);  /* get the metatable */
01126   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01127   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".get"); /* find the .get table */
01128   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* should be a table: */
01129   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,name,getFn);
01130   lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove table) */
01131   if (setFn)  /* if there is a set fn */
01132   {
01133     SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".set"); /* find the .set table */
01134     assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* should be a table: */
01135     SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,name,setFn);
01136     lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove table) */
01137   }
01138   lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove meta) */
01139 }
01140 #endif
01141 
01142 /* adding a function module */
01143 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_module_add_function(lua_State* L,const char* name,lua_CFunction fn)
01144 {
01145   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,name,fn);
01146 }

01148 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

01151 
01152 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_namespace_get(lua_State* L)
01153 {
01154 /*  there should be 2 params passed in
01155   (1) table (not the meta table)
01156   (2) string name of the attribute
01157 */
01158   assert(lua_istable(L,-2));  /* just in case */
01159   lua_getmetatable(L,-2);
01160   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01161   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".get"); /* find the .get table */
01162   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01163   /* look for the key in the .get table */
01164   lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01165   lua_rawget(L,-2);
01166   lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove .get table */
01167   if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))
01168   {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01169     lua_call(L,0,1);  /* 1 value in (userdata),1 out (result) */
01170     lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove metatable */
01171     return 1;
01172   }
01173   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove whatever was there */
01174   /* ok, so try the .fn table */
01175   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".fn"); /* find the .get table */
01176   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01177   lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01178   lua_rawget(L,-2);  /* look for the fn */
01179   lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove .fn table */
01180   if (lua_isfunction(L,-1)) /* note: whether it's a C function or lua function */
01181   {  /* found it so return the fn & let lua call it */
01182     lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove metatable */
01183     return 1;
01184   }
01185   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove whatever was there */
01186   return 0;
01187 }
01188 
01189 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_namespace_set(lua_State* L)
01190 {
01191 /*  there should be 3 params passed in
01192   (1) table (not the meta table)
01193   (2) string name of the attribute
01194   (3) any for the new value
01195 */
01196 
01197   assert(lua_istable(L,1));
01198   lua_getmetatable(L,1);    /* get the meta table */
01199   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01200 
01201   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".set"); /* find the .set table */
01202   if (lua_istable(L,-1))
01203   {
01204     /* look for the key in the .set table */
01205     lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01206     lua_rawget(L,-2);
01207     if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))
01208     {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01209       lua_pushvalue(L,3);  /* value */
01210       lua_call(L,1,0);
01211       return 0;
01212     }
01213     lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the value */
01214   }
01215   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the value .set table */
01216   return 0;
01217 }
01218 
01219 SWIGINTERN void SWIG_Lua_InstallConstants(lua_State* L, swig_lua_const_info constants[]); // forward declaration
01220 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_add_class_variable(lua_State* L,const char* name,lua_CFunction getFn,lua_CFunction setFn); // forward declaration
01221 
01222 /* helper function - register namespace methods and attributes into namespace */
01223 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_add_namespace_details(lua_State* L, swig_lua_namespace* ns)
01224 {
01225   int i = 0;
01226   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01227   /* There must be table at the top of the stack */
01228   SWIG_Lua_InstallConstants(L, ns->ns_constants);
01229 
01230   lua_getmetatable(L,-1);
01231 
01232   /* add fns */
01233   for(i=0;ns->ns_attributes[i].name;i++){
01234     SWIG_Lua_add_class_variable(L,ns->ns_attributes[i].name,ns->ns_attributes[i].getmethod,ns->ns_attributes[i].setmethod);
01235   }
01236 
01237   /* add methods to the metatable */
01238   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".fn"); /* find the .fn table */
01239   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01240   for(i=0;ns->ns_methods[i].name;i++){
01241     SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,ns->ns_methods[i].name,ns->ns_methods[i].method);
01242   }
01243   lua_pop(L,1);
01244 
01245   /* clear stack - remove metatble */
01246   lua_pop(L,1);
01247   return 0;
01248 
01249 }
01250 
01251 /* helper function. creates namespace table and add it to module table */
01252 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_namespace_register(lua_State* L, swig_lua_namespace* ns)
01253 {
01254   assert(lua_istable(L,-1)); /* just in case. This is supposed to be module table */
01255   lua_checkstack(L,5);
01256   lua_pushstring(L, ns->name);
01257   lua_newtable(L); /* namespace itself */
01258   lua_newtable(L); /* metatable for namespace */
01259 
01260   /* add a table called ".get" */
01261   lua_pushstring(L,".get");
01262   lua_newtable(L);
01263   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01264   /* add a table called ".set" */
01265   lua_pushstring(L,".set");
01266   lua_newtable(L);
01267   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01268   /* add a table called ".fn" */
01269   lua_pushstring(L,".fn");
01270   lua_newtable(L);
01271   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01272 
01273   /* add accessor fns for using the .get,.set&.fn */
01274   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__index",SWIG_Lua_namespace_get);
01275   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__newindex",SWIG_Lua_namespace_set);
01276 
01277   lua_setmetatable(L,-2); /* set metatable */
01278   lua_rawset(L,-3); /* add namespace to module table */
01279   return 0;
01280 }

01285 /* the class.get method, performs the lookup of class attributes */
01286 SWIGINTERN int  SWIG_Lua_class_get(lua_State* L)
01287 {
01288 /*  there should be 2 params passed in
01289   (1) userdata (not the meta table)
01290   (2) string name of the attribute
01291 */
01292   assert(lua_isuserdata(L,-2));  /* just in case */
01293   lua_getmetatable(L,-2);    /* get the meta table */
01294   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01295   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".get"); /* find the .get table */
01296   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01297   /* look for the key in the .get table */
01298   lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01299   lua_rawget(L,-2);
01300   lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove .get table */
01301   if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))
01302   {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01303     lua_pushvalue(L,1);  /* the userdata */
01304     lua_call(L,1,1);  /* 1 value in (userdata),1 out (result) */
01305     lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove metatable */
01306     return 1;
01307   }
01308   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove whatever was there */
01309   /* ok, so try the .fn table */
01310   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".fn"); /* find the .get table */
01311   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01312   lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01313   lua_rawget(L,-2);  /* look for the fn */
01314   lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove .fn table */
01315   if (lua_isfunction(L,-1)) /* note: if its a C function or lua function */
01316   {  /* found it so return the fn & let lua call it */
01317     lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove metatable */
01318     return 1;
01319   }
01320   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove whatever was there */
01321   /* NEW: looks for the __getitem() fn
01322   this is a user provided get fn */
01323   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,"__getitem"); /* find the __getitem fn */
01324   if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))  /* if its there */
01325   {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01326     lua_pushvalue(L,1);  /* the userdata */
01327     lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* the parameter */
01328     lua_call(L,2,1);  /* 2 value in (userdata),1 out (result) */
01329     lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove metatable */
01330     return 1;
01331   }
01332   return 0;  /* sorry not known */
01333 }
01334 
01335 /* the class.set method, performs the lookup of class attributes */
01336 SWIGINTERN int  SWIG_Lua_class_set(lua_State* L)
01337 {
01338 /*  there should be 3 params passed in
01339   (1) table (not the meta table)
01340   (2) string name of the attribute
01341   (3) any for the new value
01342 printf("SWIG_Lua_class_set %p(%s) '%s' %p(%s)\n",
01343       lua_topointer(L,1),lua_typename(L,lua_type(L,1)),
01344       lua_tostring(L,2),
01345       lua_topointer(L,3),lua_typename(L,lua_type(L,3)));*/
01346 
01347   assert(lua_isuserdata(L,1));  /* just in case */
01348   lua_getmetatable(L,1);    /* get the meta table */
01349   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01350 
01351   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".set"); /* find the .set table */
01352   if (lua_istable(L,-1))
01353   {
01354     /* look for the key in the .set table */
01355     lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* key */
01356     lua_rawget(L,-2);
01357     if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))
01358     {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01359       lua_pushvalue(L,1);  /* userdata */
01360       lua_pushvalue(L,3);  /* value */
01361       lua_call(L,2,0);
01362       return 0;
01363     }
01364     lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the value */
01365   }
01366   lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the value .set table */
01367   /* NEW: looks for the __setitem() fn
01368   this is a user provided set fn */
01369   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,"__setitem"); /* find the fn */
01370   if (lua_iscfunction(L,-1))  /* if its there */
01371   {  /* found it so call the fn & return its value */
01372     lua_pushvalue(L,1);  /* the userdata */
01373     lua_pushvalue(L,2);  /* the parameter */
01374     lua_pushvalue(L,3);  /* the value */
01375     lua_call(L,3,0);  /* 3 values in ,0 out */
01376     lua_remove(L,-2); /* stack tidy, remove metatable */
01377     return 1;
01378   }
01379   return 0;
01380 }
01381 
01382 /* the class.destruct method called by the interpreter */
01383 SWIGINTERN int  SWIG_Lua_class_destruct(lua_State* L)
01384 {
01385 /*  there should be 1 params passed in
01386   (1) userdata (not the meta table) */
01387   swig_lua_userdata* usr;
01388   swig_lua_class* clss;
01389   assert(lua_isuserdata(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01390   usr=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_touserdata(L,-1);  /* get it */
01391   /* if must be destroyed & has a destructor */
01392   if (usr->own) /* if must be destroyed */
01393   {
01394     clss=(swig_lua_class*)usr->type->clientdata;  /* get the class */
01395     if (clss && clss->destructor)  /* there is a destroy fn */
01396     {
01397       clss->destructor(usr->ptr);  /* bye bye */
01398     }
01399   }
01400   return 0;
01401 }
01402 
01403 /* the class.__tostring method called by the interpreter and print */
01404 SWIGINTERN int  SWIG_Lua_class_tostring(lua_State* L)
01405 {
01406 /*  there should be 1 param passed in
01407   (1) userdata (not the metatable) */
01408   assert(lua_isuserdata(L,1));  /* just in case */
01409   unsigned long userData = (unsigned long)lua_touserdata(L,1); /* get the userdata address for later */
01410   lua_getmetatable(L,1);    /* get the meta table */
01411   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01412   
01413   lua_getfield(L, -1, ".type");
01414   const char* className = lua_tostring(L, -1);
01415   
01416   char output[256];
01417   sprintf(output, "<%s userdata: %lX>", className, userData);
01418   
01419   lua_pushstring(L, (const char*)output);
01420   return 1;
01421 }
01422 
01423 /* to manually disown some userdata */
01424 SWIGINTERN int  SWIG_Lua_class_disown(lua_State* L)
01425 {
01426 /*  there should be 1 params passed in
01427   (1) userdata (not the meta table) */
01428   swig_lua_userdata* usr;
01429   assert(lua_isuserdata(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01430   usr=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_touserdata(L,-1);  /* get it */
01431   
01432   usr->own = 0; /* clear our ownership */
01433   return 0;
01434 }
01435 
01436 /* Constructor proxy. Used when class name entry in module is not class constructor,
01437 but special table instead. */
01438 SWIGINTERN int SWIG_Lua_constructor_proxy(lua_State* L)
01439 {
01440   /* unlimited number of parameters
01441      First one is our proxy table and we should remove it
01442      Other we should pass to real constructor
01443    */
01444    assert(lua_istable(L,1));
01445    lua_pushstring(L,".constructor");
01446    lua_rawget(L,1);
01447    assert(!lua_isnil(L,-1));
01448    lua_replace(L,1); /* replace our table with real constructor */
01449    lua_call(L,lua_gettop(L)-1,1);
01450    return 1;
01451 }
01452 
01453 /* gets the swig class registry (or creates it) */
01454 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_get_class_registry(lua_State* L)
01455 {
01456   /* add this all into the swig registry: */
01457   lua_pushstring(L,"SWIG");
01458   lua_rawget(L,LUA_REGISTRYINDEX);  /* get the registry */
01459   if (!lua_istable(L,-1))  /* not there */
01460   {  /* must be first time, so add it */
01461     lua_pop(L,1);  /* remove the result */
01462     lua_pushstring(L,"SWIG");
01463     lua_newtable(L);
01464     lua_rawset(L,LUA_REGISTRYINDEX);
01465     /* then get it */
01466     lua_pushstring(L,"SWIG");
01467     lua_rawget(L,LUA_REGISTRYINDEX);
01468   }
01469 }
01470 
01471 /* helper fn to get the classes metatable from the register */
01472 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_get_class_metatable(lua_State* L,const char* cname)
01473 {
01474   SWIG_Lua_get_class_registry(L);  /* get the registry */
01475   lua_pushstring(L,cname);  /* get the name */
01476   lua_rawget(L,-2);    /* get it */
01477   lua_remove(L,-2);    /* tidy up (remove registry) */
01478 }

01480 /* helper add a variable to a registered class */
01481 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_add_class_variable(lua_State* L,const char* name,lua_CFunction getFn,lua_CFunction setFn)
01482 {
01483   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01484   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".get"); /* find the .get table */
01485   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01486   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,name,getFn);
01487   lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove table) */
01488   if (setFn)
01489   {
01490     SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".set"); /* find the .set table */
01491     assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01492     SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,name,setFn);
01493     lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove table) */
01494   }
01495 }
01496 
01497 /* helper to recursively add class static details (static attributes, operations and constants) */
01498 SWIGINTERN void SWIG_Lua_add_class_static_details(lua_State* L, swig_lua_class* clss)
01499 {
01500   int i = 0;
01501   /* The class namespace table must be on the top of the stack */
01502   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));
01503   /* call all the base classes first: we can then override these later: */
01504   for(i=0;clss->bases[i];i++)
01505   {
01506     SWIG_Lua_add_class_static_details(L,clss->bases[i]);
01507   }
01508 
01509   SWIG_Lua_add_namespace_details(L, &clss->cls_static);
01510 }
01511 
01512 /* helper to recursively add class details (attributes & operations) */
01513 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_add_class_details(lua_State* L,swig_lua_class* clss)
01514 {
01515   int i;
01516   /* call all the base classes first: we can then override these later: */
01517   for(i=0;clss->bases[i];i++)
01518   {
01519     SWIG_Lua_add_class_details(L,clss->bases[i]);
01520   }
01521   /* add fns */
01522   for(i=0;clss->attributes[i].name;i++){
01523     SWIG_Lua_add_class_variable(L,clss->attributes[i].name,clss->attributes[i].getmethod,clss->attributes[i].setmethod);
01524   }
01525   /* add methods to the metatable */
01526   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,".fn"); /* find the .fn table */
01527   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01528   for(i=0;clss->methods[i].name;i++){
01529     SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,clss->methods[i].name,clss->methods[i].method);
01530   }
01531   lua_pop(L,1);       /* tidy stack (remove table) */
01532   /*   add operator overloads
01533     these look ANY method which start with "__" and assume they
01534     are operator overloads & add them to the metatable
01535     (this might mess up is someone defines a method __gc (the destructor)*/
01536   for(i=0;clss->methods[i].name;i++){
01537     if (clss->methods[i].name[0]=='_' && clss->methods[i].name[1]=='_'){
01538       SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,clss->methods[i].name,clss->methods[i].method);
01539     }
01540   }
01541 }
01542 
01543 /* set up the base classes pointers.
01544 Each class structure has a list of pointers to the base class structures.
01545 This function fills them.
01546 It cannot be done at compile time, as this will not work with hireachies
01547 spread over more than one swig file. 
01548 Therefore it must be done at runtime, querying the SWIG type system.
01549 */
01550 SWIGINTERN void SWIG_Lua_init_base_class(lua_State* L,swig_lua_class* clss)
01551 {
01552   int i=0;
01553   swig_module_info* module=SWIG_GetModule(L);
01554   for(i=0;clss->base_names[i];i++)
01555   {
01556     if (clss->bases[i]==0) /* not found yet */
01557     {
01558       /* lookup and cache the base class */
01559       swig_type_info *info = SWIG_TypeQueryModule(module,module,clss->base_names[i]);
01560       if (info) clss->bases[i] = (swig_lua_class *) info->clientdata;
01561     }
01562   }
01563 }
01564 
01565 /* Register class static methods,attributes etc as well as constructor proxy */
01566 SWIGINTERN void SWIG_Lua_class_register_static(lua_State* L, swig_lua_class* clss)
01567 {
01568   lua_checkstack(L,5); /* just in case */
01569   assert(lua_istable(L,-1));  /* just in case */
01570   assert(strcmp(clss->name, clss->cls_static.name) == 0); /* in class those 2 must be equal */
01571 
01572   SWIG_Lua_namespace_register(L,&clss->cls_static);
01573 
01574   SWIG_Lua_get_table(L,clss->name); // Get namespace table back
01575   assert(lua_istable(L,-1)); /* just in case */
01576 
01577   /*  add its constructor to module with the name of the class
01578   so you can do MyClass(...) as well as new_MyClass(...)
01579   BUT only if a constructor is defined
01580   (this overcomes the problem of pure virtual classes without constructors)*/
01581   if (clss->constructor)
01582   {
01583     SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,".constructor", clss->constructor);
01584     lua_getmetatable(L,-1);
01585     assert(lua_istable(L,-1)); /* just in case */
01586     SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__call", SWIG_Lua_constructor_proxy);
01587     lua_pop(L,1);
01588   }
01589 
01590   assert(lua_istable(L,-1)); /* just in case */
01591   SWIG_Lua_add_class_static_details(L, clss);
01592 
01593   /* clear stack */
01594   lua_pop(L,1);
01595 }
01596 
01597 /* performs the entire class registration process */
01598 SWIGINTERN void  SWIG_Lua_class_register(lua_State* L,swig_lua_class* clss)
01599 {
01600   SWIG_Lua_class_register_static(L,clss);
01601 
01602   SWIG_Lua_get_class_registry(L);  /* get the registry */
01603   lua_pushstring(L,clss->name);  /* get the name */
01604   lua_newtable(L);    /* create the metatable */
01605   /* add string of class name called ".type" */
01606   lua_pushstring(L,".type");
01607   lua_pushstring(L,clss->name);
01608   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01609   /* add a table called ".get" */
01610   lua_pushstring(L,".get");
01611   lua_newtable(L);
01612   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01613   /* add a table called ".set" */
01614   lua_pushstring(L,".set");
01615   lua_newtable(L);
01616   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01617   /* add a table called ".fn" */
01618   lua_pushstring(L,".fn");
01619   lua_newtable(L);
01620   /* add manual disown method */
01621   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__disown",SWIG_Lua_class_disown);
01622   lua_rawset(L,-3);
01623   /* add accessor fns for using the .get,.set&.fn */
01624   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__index",SWIG_Lua_class_get);
01625   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__newindex",SWIG_Lua_class_set);
01626   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__gc",SWIG_Lua_class_destruct);
01627   /* add tostring method for better output */
01628   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"__tostring",SWIG_Lua_class_tostring);
01629   /* add it */
01630   lua_rawset(L,-3);  /* metatable into registry */
01631   lua_pop(L,1);      /* tidy stack (remove registry) */
01632 
01633   SWIG_Lua_get_class_metatable(L,clss->name);
01634   SWIG_Lua_add_class_details(L,clss);  /* recursive adding of details (atts & ops) */
01635   lua_pop(L,1);      /* tidy stack (remove class metatable) */
01636 }

01642 /* helper to add metatable to new lua object */
01643 SWIGINTERN void _SWIG_Lua_AddMetatable(lua_State* L,swig_type_info *type)
01644 {
01645   if (type->clientdata)  /* there is clientdata: so add the metatable */
01646   {
01647     SWIG_Lua_get_class_metatable(L,((swig_lua_class*)(type->clientdata))->name);
01648     if (lua_istable(L,-1))
01649     {
01650       lua_setmetatable(L,-2);
01651     }
01652     else
01653     {
01654       lua_pop(L,1);
01655     }
01656   }
01657 }
01658 
01659 /* pushes a new object into the lua stack */
01660 SWIGRUNTIME void SWIG_Lua_NewPointerObj(lua_State* L,void* ptr,swig_type_info *type, int own)
01661 {
01662   swig_lua_userdata* usr;
01663   if (!ptr){
01664     lua_pushnil(L);
01665     return;
01666   }
01667   usr=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_newuserdata(L,sizeof(swig_lua_userdata));  /* get data */
01668   usr->ptr=ptr;  /* set the ptr */
01669   usr->type=type;
01670   usr->own=own;
01671 #if (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC)
01672   _SWIG_Lua_AddMetatable(L,type); /* add metatable */
01673 #endif
01674 }
01675 
01676 /* takes a object from the lua stack & converts it into an object of the correct type
01677  (if possible) */
01678 SWIGRUNTIME int  SWIG_Lua_ConvertPtr(lua_State* L,int index,void** ptr,swig_type_info *type,int flags)
01679 {
01680   swig_lua_userdata* usr;
01681   swig_cast_info *cast;
01682   if (lua_isnil(L,index)){*ptr=0; return SWIG_OK;}    /* special case: lua nil => NULL pointer */
01683   usr=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_touserdata(L,index);  /* get data */
01684   if (usr)
01685   {
01686     if (flags & SWIG_POINTER_DISOWN) /* must disown the object */
01687     {
01688         usr->own=0;
01689     }
01690     if (!type)            /* special cast void*, no casting fn */
01691     {
01692       *ptr=usr->ptr;
01693       return SWIG_OK; /* ok */
01694     }
01695     cast=SWIG_TypeCheckStruct(usr->type,type); /* performs normal type checking */
01696     if (cast)
01697     {
01698       int newmemory = 0;
01699       *ptr=SWIG_TypeCast(cast,usr->ptr,&newmemory);
01700       assert(!newmemory); /* newmemory handling not yet implemented */
01701       return SWIG_OK;  /* ok */
01702     }
01703   }
01704   return SWIG_ERROR;  /* error */
01705 }
01706 
01707 SWIGRUNTIME void* SWIG_Lua_MustGetPtr(lua_State* L,int index,swig_type_info *type,int flags,
01708        int argnum,const char* func_name){
01709   void* result;
01710   if (!SWIG_IsOK(SWIG_ConvertPtr(L,index,&result,type,flags))){
01711     luaL_error (L,"Error in %s, expected a %s at argument number %d\n",
01712                 func_name,(type && type->str)?type->str:"void*",argnum);
01713   }
01714   return result;
01715 }
01716 
01717 /* pushes a packed userdata. user for member fn pointers only */
01718 SWIGRUNTIME void SWIG_Lua_NewPackedObj(lua_State* L,void* ptr,size_t size,swig_type_info *type)
01719 {
01720   swig_lua_rawdata* raw;
01721   assert(ptr); /* not acceptable to pass in a NULL value */
01722   raw=(swig_lua_rawdata*)lua_newuserdata(L,sizeof(swig_lua_rawdata)-1+size);  /* alloc data */
01723   raw->type=type;
01724   raw->own=0;
01725   memcpy(raw->data,ptr,size); /* copy the data */
01726   _SWIG_Lua_AddMetatable(L,type); /* add metatable */
01727 }
01728     
01729 /* converts a packed userdata. user for member fn pointers only */
01730 SWIGRUNTIME int  SWIG_Lua_ConvertPacked(lua_State* L,int index,void* ptr,size_t size,swig_type_info *type)
01731 {
01732   swig_lua_rawdata* raw;
01733   raw=(swig_lua_rawdata*)lua_touserdata(L,index);  /* get data */
01734   if (!raw) return SWIG_ERROR;  /* error */
01735   if (type==0 || type==raw->type) /* void* or identical type */
01736   {
01737     memcpy(ptr,raw->data,size); /* copy it */
01738     return SWIG_OK; /* ok */
01739   }
01740   return SWIG_ERROR;  /* error */
01741 }
01742 
01743 /* a function to get the typestring of a piece of data */
01744 SWIGRUNTIME const char *SWIG_Lua_typename(lua_State *L, int tp)
01745 {
01746   swig_lua_userdata* usr;
01747   if (lua_isuserdata(L,tp))
01748   {
01749     usr=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_touserdata(L,tp);  /* get data */
01750     if (usr && usr->type && usr->type->str)
01751       return usr->type->str;
01752     return "userdata (unknown type)";
01753   }
01754   return lua_typename(L,lua_type(L,tp));
01755 }
01756 
01757 /* lua callable function to get the userdata's type */
01758 SWIGRUNTIME int SWIG_Lua_type(lua_State* L)
01759 {
01760   lua_pushstring(L,SWIG_Lua_typename(L,1));
01761   return 1;
01762 }
01763 
01764 /* lua callable function to compare userdata's value
01765 the issue is that two userdata may point to the same thing
01766 but to lua, they are different objects */
01767 SWIGRUNTIME int SWIG_Lua_equal(lua_State* L)
01768 {
01769   int result;
01770   swig_lua_userdata *usr1,*usr2;
01771   if (!lua_isuserdata(L,1) || !lua_isuserdata(L,2))  /* just in case */
01772     return 0;  /* nil reply */
01773   usr1=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_touserdata(L,1);  /* get data */
01774   usr2=(swig_lua_userdata*)lua_touserdata(L,2);  /* get data */
01775   /*result=(usr1->ptr==usr2->ptr && usr1->type==usr2->type); only works if type is the same*/
01776   result=(usr1->ptr==usr2->ptr);
01777    lua_pushboolean(L,result);
01778   return 1;
01779 }

01785 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) && (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
01786 /* Install Constants */
01787 SWIGINTERN void
01788 SWIG_Lua_InstallConstants(lua_State* L, swig_lua_const_info constants[]) {
01789   int i;
01790   for (i = 0; constants[i].type; i++) {
01791     switch(constants[i].type) {
01792     case SWIG_LUA_INT:
01793       lua_pushstring(L,constants[i].name);
01794       lua_pushnumber(L,(lua_Number)constants[i].lvalue);
01795       lua_rawset(L,-3);
01796       break;
01797     case SWIG_LUA_FLOAT:
01798       lua_pushstring(L,constants[i].name);
01799       lua_pushnumber(L,(lua_Number)constants[i].dvalue);
01800       lua_rawset(L,-3);
01801       break;
01802     case SWIG_LUA_CHAR:
01803       lua_pushstring(L,constants[i].name);
01804       lua_pushfstring(L,"%c",(char)constants[i].lvalue);
01805       lua_rawset(L,-3);
01806       break;
01807     case SWIG_LUA_STRING:
01808       lua_pushstring(L,constants[i].name);
01809       lua_pushstring(L,(char *) constants[i].pvalue);
01810       lua_rawset(L,-3);
01811       break;
01812     case SWIG_LUA_POINTER:
01813       lua_pushstring(L,constants[i].name);
01814       SWIG_NewPointerObj(L,constants[i].pvalue, *(constants[i]).ptype,0);
01815       lua_rawset(L,-3);
01816       break;
01817     case SWIG_LUA_BINARY:
01818       lua_pushstring(L,constants[i].name);
01819       SWIG_NewMemberObj(L,constants[i].pvalue,constants[i].lvalue,*(constants[i]).ptype);
01820       lua_rawset(L,-3);
01821       break;
01822     default:
01823       break;
01824     }
01825   }
01826 }

01833 #ifndef SWIG_DOSTRING_FAIL /* Allows redefining of error function */
01834 #define SWIG_DOSTRING_FAIL(S) fprintf(stderr,"%s\n",S)
01835 #endif
01836 /* Executes a C string in Lua which is a really simple way of calling lua from C
01837 Unfortunately lua keeps changing its APIs, so we need a conditional compile
01838 In lua 5.0.X its lua_dostring()
01839 In lua 5.1.X its luaL_dostring()
01840 */
01841 SWIGINTERN int 
01842 SWIG_Lua_dostring(lua_State *L, const char* str) {
01843   int ok,top;
01844   if (str==0 || str[0]==0) return 0; /* nothing to do */
01845   top=lua_gettop(L); /* save stack */
01846 #if (defined(LUA_VERSION_NUM) && (LUA_VERSION_NUM>=501))
01847   ok=luaL_dostring(L,str);      /* looks like this is lua 5.1.X or later, good */
01848 #else
01849   ok=lua_dostring(L,str);       /* might be lua 5.0.x, using lua_dostring */
01850 #endif
01851   if (ok!=0) {
01852     SWIG_DOSTRING_FAIL(lua_tostring(L,-1));
01853   }
01854   lua_settop(L,top); /* restore the stack */
01855   return ok;
01856 }

16084 
16085 /* -------- TYPE CONVERSION AND EQUIVALENCE RULES (END) -------- */
16086 
16087 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16088  * Type initialization:
16089  * This problem is tough by the requirement that no dynamic
16090  * memory is used. Also, since swig_type_info structures store pointers to
16091  * swig_cast_info structures and swig_cast_info structures store pointers back
16092  * to swig_type_info structures, we need some lookup code at initialization.
16093  * The idea is that swig generates all the structures that are needed.
16094  * The runtime then collects these partially filled structures.
16095  * The SWIG_InitializeModule function takes these initial arrays out of
16096  * swig_module, and does all the lookup, filling in the swig_module.types
16097  * array with the correct data and linking the correct swig_cast_info
16098  * structures together.
16099  *
16100  * The generated swig_type_info structures are assigned staticly to an initial
16101  * array. We just loop through that array, and handle each type individually.
16102  * First we lookup if this type has been already loaded, and if so, use the
16103  * loaded structure instead of the generated one. Then we have to fill in the
16104  * cast linked list. The cast data is initially stored in something like a
16105  * two-dimensional array. Each row corresponds to a type (there are the same
16106  * number of rows as there are in the swig_type_initial array). Each entry in
16107  * a column is one of the swig_cast_info structures for that type.
16108  * The cast_initial array is actually an array of arrays, because each row has
16109  * a variable number of columns. So to actually build the cast linked list,
16110  * we find the array of casts associated with the type, and loop through it
16111  * adding the casts to the list. The one last trick we need to do is making
16112  * sure the type pointer in the swig_cast_info struct is correct.
16113  *
16114  * First off, we lookup the cast->type name to see if it is already loaded.
16115  * There are three cases to handle:
16116  *  1) If the cast->type has already been loaded AND the type we are adding
16117  *     casting info to has not been loaded (it is in this module), THEN we
16118  *     replace the cast->type pointer with the type pointer that has already
16119  *     been loaded.
16120  *  2) If BOTH types (the one we are adding casting info to, and the
16121  *     cast->type) are loaded, THEN the cast info has already been loaded by
16122  *     the previous module so we just ignore it.
16123  *  3) Finally, if cast->type has not already been loaded, then we add that
16124  *     swig_cast_info to the linked list (because the cast->type) pointer will
16125  *     be correct.
16126  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
16127 
16128 #ifdef __cplusplus
16129 extern "C" {
16130 #if 0
16131 } /* c-mode */
16132 #endif
16133 #endif
16134 
16135 #if 0
16136 #define SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16137 #endif
16138 
16139 
16140 SWIGRUNTIME void
16141 SWIG_InitializeModule(void *clientdata) {
16142   size_t i;
16143   swig_module_info *module_head, *iter;
16144   int found, init;
16145 
16146   /* check to see if the circular list has been setup, if not, set it up */
16147   if (swig_module.next==0) {
16148     /* Initialize the swig_module */
16149     swig_module.type_initial = swig_type_initial;
16150     swig_module.cast_initial = swig_cast_initial;
16151     swig_module.next = &swig_module;
16152     init = 1;
16153   } else {
16154     init = 0;
16155   }
16156 
16157   /* Try and load any already created modules */
16158   module_head = SWIG_GetModule(clientdata);
16159   if (!module_head) {
16160     /* This is the first module loaded for this interpreter */
16161     /* so set the swig module into the interpreter */
16162     SWIG_SetModule(clientdata, &swig_module);
16163     module_head = &swig_module;
16164   } else {
16165     /* the interpreter has loaded a SWIG module, but has it loaded this one? */
16166     found=0;
16167     iter=module_head;
16168     do {
16169       if (iter==&swig_module) {
16170         found=1;
16171         break;
16172       }
16173       iter=iter->next;
16174     } while (iter!= module_head);
16175 
16176     /* if the is found in the list, then all is done and we may leave */
16177     if (found) return;
16178     /* otherwise we must add out module into the list */
16179     swig_module.next = module_head->next;
16180     module_head->next = &swig_module;
16181   }
16182 
16183   /* When multiple interpreters are used, a module could have already been initialized in
16184      a different interpreter, but not yet have a pointer in this interpreter.
16185      In this case, we do not want to continue adding types... everything should be
16186      set up already */
16187   if (init == 0) return;
16188 
16189   /* Now work on filling in swig_module.types */
16190 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16191   printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: size %d\n", swig_module.size);
16192 #endif
16193   for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
16194     swig_type_info *type = 0;
16195     swig_type_info *ret;
16196     swig_cast_info *cast;
16197 
16198 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16199     printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: type %d %s\n", i, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
16200 #endif
16201 
16202     /* if there is another module already loaded */
16203     if (swig_module.next != &swig_module) {
16204       type = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module.next, &swig_module, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
16205     }
16206     if (type) {
16207       /* Overwrite clientdata field */
16208 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16209       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found type %s\n", type->name);
16210 #endif
16211       if (swig_module.type_initial[i]->clientdata) {
16212         type->clientdata = swig_module.type_initial[i]->clientdata;
16213 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16214       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found and overwrite type %s \n", type->name);
16215 #endif
16216       }
16217     } else {
16218       type = swig_module.type_initial[i];
16219     }
16220 
16221     /* Insert casting types */
16222     cast = swig_module.cast_initial[i];
16223     while (cast->type) {
16224 
16225       /* Don't need to add information already in the list */
16226       ret = 0;
16227 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16228       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: look cast %s\n", cast->type->name);
16229 #endif
16230       if (swig_module.next != &swig_module) {
16231         ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module.next, &swig_module, cast->type->name);
16232 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16233         if (ret) printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found cast %s\n", ret->name);
16234 #endif
16235       }
16236       if (ret) {
16237         if (type == swig_module.type_initial[i]) {
16238 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16239           printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: skip old type %s\n", ret->name);
16240 #endif
16241           cast->type = ret;
16242           ret = 0;
16243         } else {
16244           /* Check for casting already in the list */
16245           swig_cast_info *ocast = SWIG_TypeCheck(ret->name, type);
16246 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16247           if (ocast) printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: skip old cast %s\n", ret->name);
16248 #endif
16249           if (!ocast) ret = 0;
16250         }
16251       }
16252 
16253       if (!ret) {
16254 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16255         printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: adding cast %s\n", cast->type->name);
16256 #endif
16257         if (type->cast) {
16258           type->cast->prev = cast;
16259           cast->next = type->cast;
16260         }
16261         type->cast = cast;
16262       }
16263       cast++;
16264     }
16265     /* Set entry in modules->types array equal to the type */
16266     swig_module.types[i] = type;
16267   }
16268   swig_module.types[i] = 0;
16269 
16270 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16271   printf("**** SWIG_InitializeModule: Cast List ******\n");
16272   for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
16273     int j = 0;
16274     swig_cast_info *cast = swig_module.cast_initial[i];
16275     printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: type %d %s\n", i, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
16276     while (cast->type) {
16277       printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: cast type %s\n", cast->type->name);
16278       cast++;
16279       ++j;
16280     }
16281   printf("---- Total casts: %d\n",j);
16282   }
16283   printf("**** SWIG_InitializeModule: Cast List ******\n");
16284 #endif
16285 }
16286 
16287 /* This function will propagate the clientdata field of type to
16288 * any new swig_type_info structures that have been added into the list
16289 * of equivalent types.  It is like calling
16290 * SWIG_TypeClientData(type, clientdata) a second time.
16291 */
16292 SWIGRUNTIME void
16293 SWIG_PropagateClientData(void) {
16294   size_t i;
16295   swig_cast_info *equiv;
16296   static int init_run = 0;
16297 
16298   if (init_run) return;
16299   init_run = 1;
16300 
16301   for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; i++) {
16302     if (swig_module.types[i]->clientdata) {
16303       equiv = swig_module.types[i]->cast;
16304       while (equiv) {
16305         if (!equiv->converter) {
16306           if (equiv->type && !equiv->type->clientdata)
16307             SWIG_TypeClientData(equiv->type, swig_module.types[i]->clientdata);
16308         }
16309         equiv = equiv->next;
16310       }
16311     }
16312   }
16313 }

16315 #ifdef __cplusplus
16316 #if 0
16317 { /* c-mode */
16318 #endif
16319 }
16320 #endif

16324 /* Forward declaration of where the user's %init{} gets inserted */
16325 void SWIG_init_user(lua_State* L );
16326     
16327 #ifdef __cplusplus
16328 extern "C" {
16329 #endif
16330 /* this is the initialization function
16331   added at the very end of the code
16332   the function is always called SWIG_init, but an earlier #define will rename it
16333 */
16334 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) || (SWIG_LUA_TARGET == SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
16335 LUALIB_API int SWIG_init(lua_State* L)
16336 #else
16337 SWIGEXPORT int SWIG_init(lua_State* L) /* default Lua action */
16338 #endif
16339 {
16340 #if (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC) /* valid for both Lua and eLua */
16341   int i;
16342   /* start with global table */
16343   lua_pushglobaltable (L);
16344   /* SWIG's internal initalisation */
16345   SWIG_InitializeModule((void*)L);
16346   SWIG_PropagateClientData();
16347 #endif
16348 
16349 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) && (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
16350   /* add a global fn */
16351   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"swig_type",SWIG_Lua_type);
16352   SWIG_Lua_add_function(L,"swig_equals",SWIG_Lua_equal);
16353   /* begin the module (its a table with the same name as the module) */
16354   SWIG_Lua_module_begin(L,SWIG_name);
16355   /* add commands/functions */
16356   for (i = 0; swig_commands[i].name; i++){
16357     SWIG_Lua_module_add_function(L,swig_commands[i].name,swig_commands[i].func);
16358   }
16359   /* add variables */
16360   for (i = 0; swig_variables[i].name; i++){
16361     SWIG_Lua_module_add_variable(L,swig_variables[i].name,swig_variables[i].get,swig_variables[i].set);
16362   }
16363 #endif
16364 
16365 #if (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC)
16366   /* set up base class pointers (the hierarchy) */
16367   for (i = 0; swig_types[i]; i++){
16368     if (swig_types[i]->clientdata){
16369       SWIG_Lua_init_base_class(L,(swig_lua_class*)(swig_types[i]->clientdata));
16370     }
16371   }
16372   /* additional registration structs & classes in lua */
16373   for (i = 0; swig_types[i]; i++){
16374     if (swig_types[i]->clientdata){
16375       SWIG_Lua_class_register(L,(swig_lua_class*)(swig_types[i]->clientdata));
16376     }
16377   }
16378 #endif
16379 
16380 #if ((SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUA) && (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC))
16381   /* constants */
16382   SWIG_Lua_InstallConstants(L,swig_constants);
16383 #endif
16384 
16385 #if (SWIG_LUA_TARGET != SWIG_LUA_FLAVOR_ELUAC)
16386   /* invoke user-specific initialization */
16387   SWIG_init_user(L);
16388   /* end module */
16389   /* Note: We do not clean up the stack here (Lua will do this for us). At this
16390      point, we have the globals table and out module table on the stack. Returning
16391      one value makes the module table the result of the require command. */
16392   return 1;
16393 #else
16394   return 0;
16395 #endif
16396 }

16398 #ifdef __cplusplus
16399 }
16400 #endif
